
## Project Overview
End-to-end DevOps pipeline for a Healthcare application using
Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes, Ansible, and AWS EC2.

## Tools & Technologies
- AWS EC2
- Jenkins
- Docker & DockerHub
- Kubernetes
- Ansible
- Git & GitHub
- Linux (Ubuntu)

## Architecture
- Jenkins for CI/CD
- Docker for containerization
- Kubernetes for deployment
- Ansible for tool installation

## CI/CD Pipeline Stages
1. Git Checkout
2. Maven Build
3. Docker Image Build
4. Push Image to DockerHub
5. Deploy to Kubernetes Cluster

## How to Run
1. Launch EC2 instances (Master & Worker)
2. Run Ansible playbook to install tools
3. Configure Jenkins pipeline
4. Deploy application using Kubernetes
5. Access application via NodePort

## Output
Application accessible at:
http://<Master-Public-IP>:30085
